# Windsurf Rules — Advanced Playwright Framework

## Mandatory Quality Gates
Run after every change before marking complete:
```bash
npm run typecheck                        # TypeScript — zero errors
npm run lint                             # ESLint — zero errors
npm run format:check                     # Prettier — all formatted
npx playwright test --grep @smoke        # Smoke suite — all green
```

## Architecture
- Framework: Playwright Test + TypeScript (strict)
- Pattern: Page Object Model + Custom Fixtures
- Reporting: Custom TTA Reporter + Allure + Playwright HTML
- Logging: Winston (shared logger + scoped child loggers)

## Required Patterns

### Page Object
```typescript
import { BasePage } from './BasePage';

export class LoginPage extends BasePage {
  usernameInput = () => this.page.locator('#username');

  async login(user: string, pass: string) {
    await this.usernameInput().fill(user);
  }
}
```

### Test File
```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@fixtures/test-base';

test('@smoke @P0 description', async ({ loginPage }) => {
  // test body
});
```

### Logger
```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@utils/logger';
const log = createLogger('MyClass');
log.info('message');
```

## Hard Rules
1. Locators = arrow functions only (prevents stale elements)
2. Every test = at least one tag
3. No `as any` or `@ts-ignore`
4. All quality gates must pass before committing
5. Files go in correct `src/` subfolder only
